courses.learning_outcomes:
By the end of this course, students should be able to:
a. Understand the policy process and its application in real life policies;
b. Understand key concepts and theoretical approaches to public sciences and analysis;
c. Adopt and apply theories to understand real world problems;
d. Formulate their own knowledge system based on the knowledge and concepts introduced.

By the end of this course, students should be able to:
a. Have a clear picture about the theory, concept, measurement, and hypothesis in research methods in policy studies;
b. Know about the main stages and approaches for conducting qualitative and quantitative research in policy studies;
c. Develop the basic skills to evaluate public policy and social programmes

By the end of this course, students should be able to:
a. Understand the process of policy making and steps and theoretical perspectives of design thinking;
b. Apply the framework of design thinking in policymaking;
c. Analyze policy from different stakeholders’ perspectives in policy design;
d. Have a solid foundation of policy design and analysis.

By the end of the course, students should be able to:
Discuss critically the (un)ethical use of AI technologies in society;
Understand the need for dedicated regulatory AI policies;
Appreciate the promising applications of AI technologies in achieving the United Nations’ Sustainable Development Goals;
Apply deep learning techniques to solve AI problems for social good.
